post_text: 5th grade Social Studies students in Mrs. Waneck's class learned what it took to survive in the Jamestown Colony by completing a mission to help Captain John Smith break the code in an escape room activity. Students had to read facts, apply their knowledge, and answer questions about Jamestown in order to decipher and decode the message and save the colonists. Many thanks to Mrs. Waneck for encouraging critical thinking and making learning fun for the students of MISD!

post_text: Mrs. Danna Hess' Algebra 2 classes collected data for the measurement of their femurs and showed they are in proportion to their height. They measured Bonapart’s femur in inches, had to convert to centimeters then plotted the data, and calculated the line of best fit. This data could be used to predict height of a person under CSI conditions in forensics or prehistoric findings. It's great to see that these students will never have to wonder how they will use Math in real life! Many thanks to Mrs. Hess for all she does to inspire our students at MISD!

ATTENTION PARENTS:
Due to heavy rains, current flooding of roads, or future potential flooding in the next few hours, we are taking all precautions to get our students home safely. Because of this, NO AFTERNOON bus routes will run, but we will dismiss at normal time (3:30 pm).

The bus route to Dynamite Daycare WILL run at normal times. Car line pick-ups will run as normal. All students may be picked up at their respective buildings.

We appreciate your patience.
Thank you!
Muenster ISD

post_text: The students in Michelle Sicking's 5th grade Reading class are learning to be accountable and responsible for their learning. As they take tests this year, the students will record their grade, what grade they would like to make on the next test, and develop a plan with the help of Miss Sicking on how they are going to achieve this grade. This will help students learn how to achieve the goals they set for themselves. It's great to see how successful Muenster Hornets are made! #GreatThingsatMISD

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Application instructions have been distributed via email to parents and a printed copy will be mailed with the final report card.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Come through the Elementary car line on Wednesday, May 20 or Thursday, May 21 from 8:00 am - 12:00 pm to pick-up school supplies, locker items, spring photos, and art projects. This is also the time to return any MISD issued Chromebooks, library books, or kindergarten graduation cap & gown.

We want to THANK YOU for a great school year and LOOK FORWARD to next year when we will see you again!

Love,
Muenster Elementary Teachers & Staff

post_text:
JH / HS Locker Clean Out Schedule

Students may enter through the front doors during scheduled times. If standing in line to get in, maintain social distancing measures while waiting. A maximum of 5 students will be allowed in the building at one time.

Once you have cleaned your locker and removed all items you will be asked to exit through the East exits.

School textbooks and other items will need to be placed in designated areas before you leave.

After exiting the buildings please do not congregate in the parking areas.

Students needing to get items from Competition Gym or Field House will need to go to the back door of the Gym or Front door of the field house to remove personal items.

All guidelines from above apply. Enter and Exit procedures will be established by coaches in the gym and field house.

May 20 - May 28 from 8:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m. will be dates and times for students to return chromebooks that were checked-out for distance learning back to the campus they received it from and any other school items that need to be returned.

Hornet Yearbook and the COVID-19 Pandemic

Our 2020 yearbook will be unique to say the least! Let’s create an annual that reaches to the highest Muenster Hornet Traditions and something to look back on how we as a Hornet family excelled and prospered during this historic time.

We are planning a COVID-19 Divider in our 2020 Yearbook. We would like to include photos from you during our Distance Learning. They could be your school work, athletic workouts, or how your family is spending time during self quarantine.

Please send you photos along with a short description of what is going on and who is in each photo as an email attachment to: rick.harris@muensterisd.org
#GreatThingsatMISD

post_text: Texas, remember the importance of social distancing. If you must go out, avoid public spaces and keep your distance from others (at least 6 feet). If we continue to follow valuable public health guidance, fewer of our friends & family will be affected by COVID-19. #StayHomeTexas
text: Texas, remember the importance of social distancing. If you must go out, avoid public spaces and keep your distance from others (at least 6 feet). If we continue to follow valuable public health guidance, fewer of our friends & family will be affected by COVID-19. #StayHomeTexas

post_text: #COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

post_text: Information from Texas Education Agency: Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

post_text: Before social distancing, each person with #COVID19 spread the virus to 2.5 more people. At that pace, most would get it, and many more people would die. But we can slow the spread. That’s why we all #StayHome. #ApartTogether we slow coronavirus.

Muenster ISD Parents, Students, and Community Members. Please read our weekly update for the COVID-19 & Distance Learning posted Friday, April 3, 2020.

SMORE.COM
Muenster ISD eNewsletter

post_text:
Though we are not together every day, we at Muenster ISD continue to support each other as a community, and right now we must work together to fight COVID-19. In order to help prevent the spread of COVID-19, MISD will be reaching out to you via email, text message, and social media over the next two weeks to share vitally important public health guidance provided through TEA and the State of Texas.

This public health guidance is based on what scientists know about how to prevent the spread of COVID-19, and it is our hope that you will do what you can to follow these practices and share them with your friends and family.

Thank you for what you are doing to educate your children at home and all the efforts you’re making to keep your family healthy and safe. We know this is a difficult time. If we stand apart as a community during this stretch and continue following the public health practices we will be sharing over the coming days, we will be back together soon.

Thank you for all you are doing to support our students through your work.

Steven L. Self

Superintendent

This weekend FCCLA went to Region II conference in Waco. Students participated in STAR events, were a part of the Connection team and were awarded for completing a unit of the National program, Power of One. Both STAR event teams are advancing to compete at the State conference in April. Congratulations to Maddie, Erica, & Taylor for placing 1st place in Sports Nutrition level 2 and to Camdyn for placing 4th in Repurpose Redesign level 1!

January 26 at 4:55 PM ·

Congratulations to the winners of our council level Knights of Columbus Free Throw Championship! First place winners will progress on to the district competition which is scheduled for Sunday, February 2 at 1:30 PM in the Nocona High School gymnasium. Competitors need to be sure to bring their entry form and a copy of their birth certificate. Here are our winners from the council level competition:

9 YO: Audrey Hartman, Dayne Sadler
10 YO: Halli Bartram, John G. Bartush
11 YO: Anna Kay Hennigan, Luke Hesse
12 YO: Danni Paulin, Simon Johnson
13 YO: Macy Bayer, Kameron Knabe
14 YO: Seth Stoffels

A special thank you to Coach Jon LeBrasseur of Sacred Heart Catholic School and Coach Jeff Presnall of Muenster ISD for the roles they play in helping coordinate the event and communicating information to their athletes.

post_text:
Muenster Elementary School has been awarded the ExxonMobil Education Alliance Grant to support Math and Science programs. As an ExxonMobil fuel distributor, Douglass Distributing, donates a check on behalf of one of our Exxon or Mobil locations. The grant of $500 was made possible by funding from the ExxonMobil Corporation through Bayer's Kolonialwaren in Muenster, Texas. This grant is part of a program that supports schools in communities that are served by Exxon Mobil stations. The ExxonMobil Education Alliance grant will be used for the next generation of students to pursue studies in math and science.

Thank you, ExxonMobil Douglass Distributing , and Bayer's Kolonialwaren!

#GreatThingsatMISD #MuensterElementary

post_text:
In an effort to keep our parents and community members informed, we wanted to let you know of a special event happening on Friday, Oct. 25.

Our students and teachers are participating in Muenster ISD's Annual Career Day on Friday, Oct. 25, where visitors are invited to speak to our students about career opportunities. As part of this event, our JH/HS students will have a visitor from the DPS tactical flight team of DFW (weather permitting). During this visit there will be a helicopter landing on campus around 9:00 a.m. We wanted everyone to be aware so there is not undue worry or concern.

If you have any questions, please contact the MISD Administration office.

post_text: #GreatThingsatMISD #MuensterBassFishingTeam
shared_text:
Monica Ashley Huchton‎MHS Bass Fishing Team
September 21, 2019 at 5:38 PM ·

Pretty successful day for MHS Bass Fishing Team. It was a rough windy day on the water & four out of five of our teams weighed in fish at today’s tournament. Stephen Dangelmayr won Big Bass award & a new pair of Costa Sunglasses and team of Stephen Dangelmayr & Cade Huchton placed 6th out of 174 teams & won new Lews Reels. Great job MHS anglers! And a huge thank you to Prudy Bayer with Mossy Oak Properties for sponsoring our team! We love our jerseys & team tent.
